  "historyText": "Who Blidworth Welfare FC Are — and Where to Find Us\nBlidworth Welfare Football Club is a community football club based in the former mining village of Blidworth, near Mansfield in Nottinghamshire. The club plays its home games at The Welfare Ground, Mansfield Road, Blidworth, NG21 0LR, a multi-sport complex that also hosts local cricket and bowls. ()\n\nWhere is Blidworth?\nBlidworth sits roughly five miles east of Mansfield in the East Midlands. Historically part of Sherwood Forest country, the village grew rapidly with the opening of Blidworth Colliery in the 1920s and today forms a tight-knit community with its own parish council and amenities. ()\n\nA brief club history\nAlthough football in the village dates further back, the modern story begins when Folk House Old Boys adopted the name Blidworth Welfare in 1982. The club became founder members of the Northern Counties East League in the early 1980s, spent long spells in the Central Midlands League, and first entered the FA Cup in 1993–94. After winning the Central Midlands South Division in 2021–22, Blidworth earned promotion to the United Counties League for 2022–23.\n\nKey timeline highlights:\n\n1926 – Club origins as Folk House Old Boys.\n1982 – Renamed Blidworth Welfare; founder members of the NCEL.\n1993–94 – First FA Cup entry.\n2021–22 – Central Midlands South champions.\n2022–23 – Promoted to United Counties League. – Self Relagation from step 6 to step 8.\n2023-24 – CMAL East Division 1 champions.\nToday, Blidworth compete within the rebranded Abacus Lighting Central Midlands Alliance structure on the FA’s Full-Time system, with fixtures, results and player stats published there throughout the season. ()\n\nThe ground: “The Welfare”\nOur home is exactly what the name suggests: a classic East Midlands Miners’ Welfare venue. It’s on the north side of the village, sharing a wider complex with other local sports. Matchdays have that proper non-league feel—close to the action, volunteers everywhere, and the social club right on site. ()\n\nAddress for the sat-nav:\nThe Welfare Ground, Mansfield Road, Blidworth, Nottinghamshire, NG21 0LR. ()\n\nManagement and club leadership\nAs of the latest updates, Callum Harris is listed as First-Team Manager, with Chris Wain as Chairman. You’ll also find regular updates and videos from the dugout across the club’s official Facebook pages and group, which cover fixtures, goals, post-match interviews and community news. ()\n\nHow to follow and get involved\nLeague & fixtures: FA Full-Time carries Blidworth’s league fixtures, tables and stats. Bookmark it to keep track of matchdays. ()\nSocials: Follow the club’s Facebook presence (page and new group) for announcements, photos and interviews straight from The Welfare. ()\nIn short: Blidworth Welfare FC is a proud village club with deep roots in Nottinghamshire’s football and mining heritage, playing out of The Welfare in Blidworth and pushing forward under a refreshed management team. If you’re local—or just love proper non-league—come down, say hello, and be part of it",
